thread.title: Building approvals tipped to fall

title: Building approvals tipped to fall
text:
Building approvals are expected to have fallen in June after posting a strong surge the month before. 
Economists expect new data from the Australian Bureau of Statistics on Thursday will show approvals for the construction of new homes dropped 0.9 per cent in June. 
That follows an 2.4 per cent rise in May, boosted by a 16.6 per cent surge in multi unit dwellings, which includes apartment blocks and townhouses. 
Westpac economists said the June result is difficult to call because while there is a strong surge in high rise apartments, home buyer confidence is softening and there are fewer incentives for investors to enter the market. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Building approvals tipped to fall AAP
